{"id": 224999422, "title": "This Luxury Maldives Resort Is A Paradise For Snorkeling And Diving", "text": "Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Share to Linkedin Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Located in one of the world's largest and deepest natural atolls, Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa epitomizes barefoot luxury in The Maldives. With its vibrant marine life, untouched scenery and natural seclusion, this is one of the most memorable getaways in the popular island nation. Just 55 km from the Equator, the Park Hyatt Maldives is an exclusive escape: one that requires an additional seaplane and speedboat to reach paradise. But the property\u2019s far-flung location is also its greatest assets. Intrepid travelers will be rewarded by coming up-close-and-personal with some of the most colorful sea life in the Indian Ocean \u2014 and nothing but shimmering turquoise waters for miles along on the horizon. Whether you\u2019re celebrating romance, bonding with your family or deep sea diving, the resort offers something for every type of traveler. Snorkeling in Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa A Living Island A veritable \u201cliving island\u201d, Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa takes a sustainable approach to luxury in the glitzy island nation. While many islands in The Maldives are manmade, with reclaimed sandbanks and chalky beaches, Park Hyatt is unique for its naturally powdery white sand which shifts over time with the tides. This means the beach is in constant flux \u2014 sometimes wider, sometimes smaller. Certified by Green Globe, a global environmental certification programme, this oasis is as natural as you get in the Maldives. And efforts are constantly being made to protect and preserve its ecological footprint. Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa MORE FOR YOU Trump Trial Prosecutor Ends Closing Argument After Nearly 5 Hours Jury Instructions Set For Wednesday Gas Explosion In Downtown Youngstown Ohio Injures At Least 7 Take Advantage Of The Best Memorial Day Laptop Sales Still Live The property\u2019s 14 overwater villas were carefully assembled with the help of divers to avoid disrupting the fragile coral on the seabed; rainwater is harvested; and ocean water is used to cool the air-conditioning units. In terms of its design, the property feels naturally beachy instead of overtly manicured. Unparalleled Underwater Experiences Famed for its extensive house reef which stretches around the perimeter of the resort, the live coral and colorful fish are a major draw for guests who return year after year. From searching for sea turtles underwater, swimming with black tip reef sharks, and spotting spinner dolphins leaping in the waves, nature abounds just steps from the shore. Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa The Maldives counts over 1,000 species of fish \u2014 many of which you can spot snorkeling including parrotfish and clownfish \u2014 while larger species can be sighted a short boat ride away. Park Hyatt Maldives has 42 dive sites and is one of the few resorts that offers diving with Tiger sharks, an exhilarating experience for adventurous guests. Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Unique activities include a dolphin cruise and turtle quest, guided nighttime snorkeling, equator excursion and stargazing cruises. For adventurous travelers, opt for a cast away \"survival experience\" where you'll be dropped off on a remote island with a picnic and dummy phone \u2014 the ultimate digital detox. Or try fishing for wahoo, jackfish or tuna which will be freshly prepared for you back on land. Luxurious Accommodations Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa With just 51 private land and water villas Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa is one of the smaller resorts in the Maldives. This intimate feeling is enhanced by attentive staff who live at the center of the resort and are available for any request, big or small, throughout the guest\u2019s stay. The design is contemporary tropical, with elegant accomodations starting at 115 sq m and featuring luxurious bathrooms (with indoor and outdoor shower, bathtub, and more), private plunge pools, and sundecks. The Overwater Sunset Pool Villa, with an outdoor cabana and infinity pool which blends in with the crystal clear sea, is ideal for romantic occasions. The resort\u2019s crown jewel is the 3-bedroom Kiaali Residence, located at the end of the pier with 360-degree views of the sea. This palatial residence, designed by Paris-based Atelier Donatien Carratier, spans 895 sqm and accommodates up to six guests. With floor-to-ceiling windows, a 16-meter-long freshwater swimming pool, whirlpool, private gym, sunken dining area, and outdoor barbecue area, it has everything you need for an unforgettable stay. The property comes with its own private chef, butler and buggy service, but we can assure you that once you check-in, you won\u2019t want to leave. The Kiaali Residence Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Creative Dining Set within an airy space overlooking the property's main pool, The Dining Room is the focal point of the hotel. Guests can enjoy \u00e0 la carte breakfast, lunch and dinner featuring a range of international and local cuisines. Nearby, The Bar is a beachy lounge space where you can enjoy meals and signature cocktails artfully prepared by the resort\u2019s bartenders. Both options are ideal for couples or families with children. Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa For more intimate dining, try Koi at The Drift. This contemporary Japanese cuisine in a unique overwater restaurant. The restaurant prioritizes sustainable seafood and local ingredients, some of which are grown in the property's own garden. Sashimi salad, yellowtail hamachi with passion fruit ponzu and freshwater eel nigiri are some of the delights you can look forward to during your meal. Vegan options are also available, including a delightful 24-hour cooked watermelon featuring tofu truffle mayo, local pine nut and basil oil. Plant-based eaters can\u2019t miss booking the Chef's Garden Treehouse featuring an all-plant based, 7-course tasting menu served in a treehouse with a view of the sunset. Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Currently, the resort has two themed evenings each week: \u201cMaldivian Night\u201d on Tuesdays which serves regional cuisine accompanied by traditional \u201cBodu Beru\u201d dance. On Saturdays, guests can enjoy a laid-back barbecue night on the beach. Relaxation and Wellbeing In addition to two spacious swimming pools, gym and a golf simulator, Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa offers luxurious wellness experiences at The Vidhun Spa. Holistic health and healing is a focus here so the spa uses local ingredients, from Maldivian fresh coconut & sea salt scrub to a poultice of thermodynamic herbs and Maldivian warm sand pouches. The spa also specializes in Ayurveda treatments, including shirodhara and abhyanga which use therapeutic oils to calm the nervous system and detoxify the body. Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa Yoga is also available according to guests desires, whether its sunrise asanas on the beach or a sunset practice in the privacy of your own villa. Aqua Yoga and Singing Bowl Meditation are also available to help guests relax and unwind, ensuring you leave The Maldives refreshed and restored. Check out my website. Livia Hengel Following Editorial Standards Print Reprints & Permissions", "summary": "Located in one of the world's deepest atolls, the Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa is a veritable \"living island\" famed for its house reef with vibrant marine life.", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/liviahengel/2024/05/29/this-luxury-maldives-resort-is-a-paradise-for-snorkeling-and-diving/", "image": "https://imageio.forbes.com/specials-images/imageserve/664d8f81d60a2363c0b2ef89/0x0.jpg?format=jpg&crop=1500,844,x0,y227,safe&height=900&width=1